<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 21 15:40:19 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
<br>
Reading these writings are very important.  Thanks to every one who finds time to write.  It's really especially helpful to read comments of persons who remained civilian through- out that war.  It's been a very long time dealing with the grief for my lost comrades and the rejection of people when we came home.  It's nice to read that civilians understand, maybe only a little bit, how tough it's been.<br><br>
I love The Wall.  I've traveled from the Midwest back to Washington to see it 6 times.  My last visit was the first time I was able to control my emotions.  It's a powerful place and I believe the spirits of the men and women we love are there.<br><br>
Semper Fi!     
